column5: Went down to 50 point today with the kids for a walk and fish a bit.  Sucks for the boat owner. http://imageshack.us/a/img17/6907/20121024182958.jpg  Hopefully it gets cleaned up soon.
Can only assume that's sitting on bottom or it would be the rest of the way down. Rain and dead batteries I bet.. or his prop shaft seals went.
Yea it is on bottom there. Water is down about 2' in there. I am not sure what caused it. I do know it is docked in another slip all summer and they have been pulling boats out now.
Through hull fitting failure? Not something I would look forward to seeing in the morning.  Bummer,  Ron...
Yep.. could be a whole new meaning to a toilet backing up!!
oh,feel the pain in the wallet there boy. at least it happened at the end of the season:sarcasm:
Hope they have a good insurer to cover that.
Was there again this morning and they had some divers there and other guys working trying to pump out the boat.  There is also a lot of gas or oil that you can see all around the marina in the water.

Was there last weekend and noticed that boat.  It's an older boat and was thinking, if they really fixed it up it would be pretty nice.  Now I see this, guess they should of fixed it up. Hopefully all oil\gas doesn't start killing off all the fish there.  Fingers crossed.
